<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q. How do I register an account?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A. You can go <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub2.ezboard.com/BBSMessageBoard.showRegistrationChoice?boardName=ascension87012">here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> to make a Global Account (which can be used on all ezBoards) or a Local Account (usable only on the Ascension Alliance Forums).  I recommend setting up a Global Account since many other EverQuest sites (www.innoruuk.com, www. Eqtraders. Com, www.eqdruids.com, etc) have ezboard forums and you would not want to go through the registration process every time you wished to post on a new site.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q. Help! I got the following message:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
You have requested access to a private forum.<br>
Please enter the access password to this forum.<br>
<br>
A. You will be asked for a password the first time you try to visit the Guild Forums or the Council Forums. To get this, email Selah at selaheq@netscape.net. Be sure to include your name in the subject line of the email so I don't delete it with all the junkmail I get!  I will usually answer within 24 hours.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q. How can I get a Custom Title?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A. Currently, the first time you post, your title will be Registered User.  Custom titles will automatically be granted to those people who are Guild Members or Council Officers, usually within a day or two of any change in status.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q.  How do I create a personal photo, a custom signature, or a personal icon?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A. Lots and lots of work in Paint Shop Pro, Adobe Photoshop, or similar graphics program!  You might start with a screenshot of yourself in game, a quote that has special meaning to you, or a pic or animation you find on the web (be sure to give credit if you borrow someone else’s work!).<br>
<br>
For tips and suggestions on how to make really nice pics, I recommend a visit to <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub16.ezboard.com/bnorrathsstudio">Norrath's Studios</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. They have a great Tips and Hints section, along with a few walkthroughs. Some people put a LOT of work into these files, animating them, creating 3D backgrounds, etc.  Go take a look – I was REALLY impressed!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q. Now that my personal photo is done, where can I store it so that I can display on the web?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A. You can store it at your personal ISP homepage or use <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.MyOwnWebOffice.com">MyOwnWebOffice</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. Don't use Geocities, Angelfire, Tripod or similar, because they don't allow remote linking and your photo will just show up as a red x or as a warning label. Don't direct link to photos found on other people's websites, since that means you're stealing bandwidth from someone else!<br>
<br>
Several suggestions for free image hosting can be found <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://beta.ezboard.com/fcooltipsntricksfrm5.showMessage?topicID=259.topic">here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q. How do I make my personal photo show up on EzBoards under my name?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A. <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.ezboard.com/help/help_howto_personalphoto.html">Personal Photo Setup</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->: Log on to EzBoards. Click on &quot;Edit Profile&quot;. Where it says &quot;Personal Photo URL&quot;, paste the URL of your picture. Don't forget to check &quot;Use personal photo&quot;. Your original picture must be 60x60 pixels or it will be distorted.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q. How do I make my personal photo show up as a signature on EzBoards?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A. <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.ezboard.com/help/help_howto_customsignature.html"> Custom Signature Setup</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->: To make the picture show in each post you make, go to your EzBoards control center.  Click on &quot;Edit Preferences&quot;. Where it says &quot;Custom Signature&quot;, write this: &lt;img src=&quot;yourURL.gif&quot;&gt; and replace “yourURL.gif” with the URL of your image, including the http:// part.  While this image can be any size, please try to keep it within reason! Under 12 standard lines in length is a good general guideline.  You can also add text before or after the image, such as a link to your Guild Magic profile or your Magelo account.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q. How do I set up a personal icon?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A. <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.ezboard.com/help/help_howto_persnlicon.html">Personal Icon Setup</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->: Please keep to the size indicated in the FAQ, and make sure it's no larger than 3k in size.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q. I've set up a custom signature or a personal photo, but it doesn't show in my posts!</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A. On the posting page, there's a section under the text entry window entitled “posting options”.  Make sure that “Include custom signature” or “Include personal photo” is marked accordingly.  In your Control Center preferences, you can set whether the default for these boxes is marked or unmarked.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q. How do I edit my post?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A. Look <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.ezboard.com/help/help_howto_editpost.html">here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q. How do I make all those cute smiley faces show up in my posts?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A. On the posting page, there's a section under the text entry window entitled “posting options”.  Click on the link entitled “Emoticons” and this will open a new window that will show you exactly what to type to make <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 0] --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/alien.gif ALT="0]"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/nerd.gif ALT="8o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  and many more!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q. How do I use ezCode to insert links and things?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A. Look <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.ezboard.com/help/help_howto_useezcodes.html">here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->!<br>
If you have a very long link, please use the ezCode (or HTML, if the forum allows it) to give a more descriptive title for viewing.  A very long, unbroken string of characters will force the page to extend and start scrolling.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q. What are the rules of etiquette on the board?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A. Just 3 basic rules!<br>
1) Please read the descriptions of all the different forums before you post to be sure that your announcement is going under the correct topic.  If it doesn't seem to fit anywhere else, Council Discussion (Council Members only), Guild Discussion (Guild Members only), or News and Views (anyone) is probably the best place for it!  Posts that seem to fit better in another category may be moved by the moderator to a more appropriate forum.<br>
<br>
2) Please show respect to the other users of the forums by refraining from arguing, insulting, and cursing.  Posts containing any of the above will probably be deleted.<br>
<br>
3) The more readable your post, the more likely it is that people will take the time to read what you've written!  Long posts should be split up into paragraphs as often as possible, and good grammar, spelling, and punctuation will make your post more readable, so please take one final minute to proofread what you have written before hitting that send button!<br>
<br>
